# Implementation Plan: Fix Course Edit Data Loss

This plan addresses the issue where editing a course causes the Overview, Other Details, Categories, and uploaded Files to be deleted or reset automatically.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - This fix strictly targets the data loss bug.
> - I will preserve existing files in the `public/home/course/` directory unless you upload a new one.
> - I will add small "Preview" links to the edit form so you can see current files before overwriting them.

## Proposed Changes

### [Admin] Course Management

#### [MODIFY] [CourseController.php](file:///mnt/WebliesNew/CareerWithoutBarrier/career-without-barrier/app/Http/Controllers/CourseController.php)
- Update the `coursesubmit` method to:
    - Retain old file paths (`notification_file_path`, `exam_details_file_path`, `prospectus`, `course_logo`, `featured_image`) if no new file is uploaded during an edit.
    - Ensure the `id` from the request is used correctly to find the existing model.

#### [MODIFY] [courses.blade.php](file:///mnt/WebliesNew/CareerWithoutBarrier/career-without-barrier/resources/views/administrator/Home/courses.blade.php)
- **Fix Textareas**: Move the `value` attribute content into the inner tag `{{ ... }}` for the CKEditor fields (`overview` and `otherdetails`).
- **Fix Dropdown**: Add `@selected($edu->id == $course->scholarship_category)` to the category loop.
- **Add Previews**: Add small links/images next to file inputs to show the current file stored in the system.

## Open Questions

- None at this stage. The bugs are technical errors in the HTML/PHP logic.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- **Test 1**: Open an existing course for editing. Verify that the Overview and Other Details are no longer empty in the CKEditor.
- **Test 2**: Change only the title of a course and save. Verify that the previously uploaded files do NOT disappear.
- **Test 3**: Verify the Category dropdown correctly shows the assigned category on page load.
